<HEADLINE> Nestle Reports Increase in Consolidated Sales </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Consolidated sales of Swiss food group
Nestle amount to 33.5 billion swiss francs (about 23 billion U.S.
dollars), an increase of 17.5 percent over the comparable period of
the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The favorable foreign exchange rates contributed nearly 11 percent
to the increase in consolidated sales, according to a press release
issued today by Nestle. 
</P>
</TEXT>
