<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Trade Integration Makes Big Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHUCHENG (Shandong), July 18 (Xinhua) -- A conference on
reforming and developing export companies is being held in
Zhucheng, in east China's Shandong province, which is known for
its successful experiment of combining farmers, manufacturers, and
trading to improve the export market.
</P>
<P>
Many Chinese farmers, manufacturers, and trading companies have
been forced to combine their business to survive in today's
competitive atmosphere as the government relaxes controls on
foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
The Zhucheng formula is one of forming a group with one or more
foreign trade companies, making regular ties with local farmers
and manufacturers by contracting out work.
</P>
<P>
Most foreign trade companies in China have no regular
suppliers. As the government gradually gives foreign trade rights
to more companies, competition for supplies and an overseas market
intensifies.
</P>
<P>
The Zhucheng Foreign Trade Group Company started with a rabbit
fur factory employing 18 workers, and ended up the biggest
supplier of chickens and natural pigment for the overseas market.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation Wu Yi said
at the conference today that the company is a trail-blazer in
developing successful county-level foreign trade enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Export-oriented enterprises at the county level are part of
China's huge foreign trade system and process most of China's farm
produce for export. However, they lack both the strength and the
outlets to compete in the overseas market.
</P>
<P>
By combining them with foreign trade companies and local farms,
it gives them the much-needed overseas market access, regular
orders, and better materials.
</P>
<P>
Wang Jinyou, general manager of the Zhucheng Foreign Trade
Group Company, said that this kind of combination is imperative
for the survival and success of local foreign trade enterprises.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
