<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, U.S. Paddlers to Commemorate "Ping Pong Diplomancy" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- World and Olympic champion Deng
Yaping and other present and former Chinese table tennis figures
will visit the United States later this month on a tour to mark
the history-making "Ping Pong Diplomacy" 25 years ago.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Table Tennis Association (CTTA) said on Friday that
joining Deng Yaping will be four members of the team which toured
the United States in 1972 -- Zhang Xielin, Zheng Minzhi, Lin
Huiqing and Qiu Yanliang.
</P>
<P>
This year's delegation, led by Xu Yinsheng, president of both
the CTTA and the International Table Tennis Federation, also
includes reigning world champions Yang Ying, Liu Guoliang, Ding
Song and coaches Cai Zhenhua and Lu Yuansheng.
</P>
<P>
In 1971, China invited the United States table tennis team to
visit China when the two countries had no diplomatic relations.
The Chinese national squad paid a return visit to the United
States in 1972.
</P>
<P>
The friendly sports exchanges played a positive role in
improving the relations of the two nations, which earned the name
of the "Ping Pong Diplomacy". China and the United States
established diplomatic relations in 1979.
</P>
<P>
The U.S delegation, which also will include U.S. table tennis
figures, will travel to China this August.
</P>
<P>
The CTTA will also stage an international table tennis
competition in Guangzhou from August 8-9, which will be
participated by top European, Asian, American and Chinese players.
</P>
<P>
The activities are organized by the CTTA, the National
Committee on U.S.-China Relations of the United States, and the
United States Table Tennis Association. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
