<HEADLINE> NPC Vice-Chairman Calls For Greater Reforms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Tian Jiyun, Vice-chairman of the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress, has called
for bolder economic reforms and speeding up the construction of
socialist democracy and legal system.
</P>
<P>
The remarks came during a visit to Nanchang, capital of east
China's Shanxi province from July 12 to 18, where Tian said that
State-owned enterprises should be bolder in their reforms. Tian
also called for greater support to such non-state enterprises as
township or private firms, and foreign-funded ones.
</P>
<P>
Tian also said that legislation should be improved and the the
people's congresses at various levels should do better in their
supervisory work.
</P>
<P>
Tian also had a close look at high-tech firms in the city and
at the planting and cultivating going on in rural areas.
</P>
