<DOCNO> XIE19970718.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Spokesman On UN Reform, Sino-Kuwaiti Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- China applauds UN
Secretary-General Kofi Annan's efforts to reform the organization
and will carefully study his reform plan, China's Foreign Ministry
Spokesman Tang Guoqiang said today.
</P>
<P>
In response to a question about the reform package that Annan
unveiled on Wednesday, Tang said that China always supports
necessary and proper reforms of the UN, to improve its efficiency,
increase its vitality, strengthen its ability to maintain world
peace and security, to promote economic and social development,
and to prepare it for the challenges of the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
China is looking forward to discussing the issue with other UN
members, he said.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that people are expecting the UN to play a
more active and effective role, especially in economic and social
development, which the developing countries are most concerned
with.
</P>
<P>
People are expecting the UN to serve its members in a better
and more comprehensive way and to live up to the purpose and
principles of the UN Charter, he said.
</P>
<P>
In response to a question about Kuwait's purchasing howitzers
from China and China's imposing conditions concerning Iraq on arms
sale to Kuwait, he said that mutually-beneficial friendly
co-operation between China and Kuwait have never involved a third
country.
</P>
<P>
Tang said that China has built its relations with Kuwait on the
basis of mutual respect and the five principles of peaceful
co-existence and that China has always supported Kuwait's stand on
safeguarding its independence, sovereignty, and territorial
integrity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
