<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Over 220 Investment Projects Approved in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 18 (Xinhua) -- The Zimbabwe Investment Centre
(ZIC), the country's investment agent, has approved 223 projects
worth 491 million U.S. Dollars during the first six months this
year, the ZIC said today.
</P>
<P>
By getting the 223 projects approved, mostly in the
commercial, manufacturing, construction and mining, the centre
injected 236 million U.S. Dollars into the country, said the ZIC.
</P>
<P>
The single largest investment of 145 million dollars is a
United States commercial venture followed by Iran which poured in
109 million U.S.Dollars worth of construction.
</P>
<P>
It was revealed that the commercial sector accounted for the
largest number of projects approved at 34, followed by
manufacturing with 27 and construction with 24.
</P>
<P>
Other sectors with significant investments include
agriculture, tourism, mining and transport.
</P>
<P>
ZIC's investment drive is being intensified to woo investors
particularly from the Far-East, North Amerfica and Australia.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
