<HEADLINE> "Missing" Students Found Safe in Northern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 17 (Xinhua) -- A group of 22 university students
who were reported missing earlier on a mountain in the northern
Philippines were found safe today, the police said.
</P>
<P>
The local Sky Cable Television quoted a police report as saying
that the first batch of the students had already come down the
1,200-meter-high Mountain Natib in Bataan province.
</P>
<P>
The police said the remaining students will leave the mountain
soon after being delayed by heavy rains which caused the mountain
path to be slippery.
</P>
<P>
The report said the students' radio signal for food and other
supplies was misunderstood as a signal for rescue by a Manila
amateur radio enthusiast Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The radio enthusiast informed the police and then hundreds of
rescuers, backed by helicopters, were sent to the area to look for
the students, who went up the mountain last weekend.  
</P>
</TEXT>
