bill and rejected an attempt to revoke China's most-favored-nation
trade status. The proposed fiscal 1998 spending, which is 1
billion dollar more than the current level, must be reconciled
with a House version expected to be passed next week.
</P>
<P>
-- Clinton will seek 350 million dollars to fund minority
teaching initiatives. Addressing the NAACP convention in
Pittsburgh, the president said his five-year race-relations
proposals aims to add 35,000 teachers in rural and inner-city
schools. He also urged resistance to calls for segregated
schooling.
</P>
