<HEADLINE> EU Grants 15 Million Dollars to Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 18 (Xinhua) -- The European Union has agreed to
grant 12.2 million European Currency Units (about 15 million U.S.
dollars) in assistance to Nepal for the second phase of its
Bagmati Watershed Management Project.
</P>
<P>
An agreement on the grant was signed recently between the two
sides, the official RSS news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Under the second phase of the project, three sub-areas of the
Bagmati catchment area -- the Kathmandu Valley, the middle Bagmati
and the Kulekhani Watershed -- will be covered.
</P>
<P>
The grant will cover about 81 percent of the project's cost.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of the project, which ended on July 15, was
also supported by the EU.  
</P>
