<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Memorial Service Held For Founder of Chinese Archaeology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Hundreds of archaeologists from
all over the country gathered in Beijing today to pay their last
respects to Prof. Su Bingqi, one of the founding fathers of
Chinese archaeology.
</P>
<P>
Su, who was president of the China Archaeology Society, died on
June 30 at the age of 88. His body was cremated today after the
memorial service.
</P>
<P>
Su was the founder of China's first archaeology major at the
prestigious Beijing University, and developed an educational
system that later came to be used by all subsequently established
archaeology faculties and departments in the country.
</P>
<P>
He developed methods like determining date according to type
and gave a structure to Chinese archaeology, explaining the growth
of Chinese civilization.
</P>
<P>
Qiao Shi, member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Central Committee of the Chinese Communist Party,
and chairman of the standing Committees of the National People's
Congress; and Li Ruihuan, member of the Standing Committee of the
Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Chinese Communist
Party and chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference, sent wreaths to the service.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
