<HEADLINE> Railway Lines In East China Interrupted By Floodwaters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Floods caused by heavy rain over
the past few days have washed across several stretches of railway
between Shanghai and a number of key cities in north China.
</P>
<P>
Many trains from Beijing, Tianjin, Shijiazhuang, Qingdao,
Jinan, Zhengzhou, and Xining to Shanghai were forced to stop en
route, and all the trains from Shanghai to those cities were
cancelled today, according to sources at the Shanghai Railway
Administration.
</P>
<P>
Railway workers and People's Liberation soldiers are making an
effort to repair the flood-damaged tracks and to get stranded
passengers to their destinations, a railway official said.
