<HEADLINE> China's Trade Minister Says Companies Should Be More Active </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHUCHENG (Shandong), July 18 (Xinhua) -- Minister of Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation Wu Yi, speaking to a conference on
reforming and developing local foreign trade enterprises today,
encouraged them to choose a style of management that best suits
them so that they will contribute more to China's foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
Wu urged the firms to increase the exports of farm and sideline
produce by integrating trade, industry and agriculture as an
important means of development.
</P>
<P>
In spite of the drop in farm and sideline produce, they still
have a certain position in foreign trade, and an increase would be
significant to China's agriculture and its foreign trade, she said.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the overseas-funded companies, some 14,000
domestic enterprises have got licenses for doing foreign trade,
2,000 of which are county or prefectural-level companies.
</P>
<P>
Wu encouraged local trading companies to increase
competitiveness through mergers or acquiring, or by establishing
enterprise groups, and said they should change their style of
management and their property rights system by re-evaluating their
property, and establish a structure with the stated-owned share in
the lead.
</P>
<P>
Managers should be under the leadership of board of directors,
she noted, and the labor, personnel and distribution of benefits
should be fundamentally reformed.
</P>
<P>
The minister also expressed the hope that local trade
enterprises will pay closer attention to the domestic market, and
get actively involved in the domestic trade business as well.
</P>
