<HEADLINE> Philippine Ruling Party Meets for 1998 Election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Manila, July 18 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine ruling Lakas-NUCD
party led by President Fidel Ramos is expected to hold a vital
meeting this evening on the selection of a party standard bearer
for the May 1998 presidential election.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Ramos will meet for the first time with all
six presidential aspirants from his Lakas-NUCD (National Union of
Christian Democrats) party, according to a press release issued by
the party's headquarters.
</P>
<P>
The statement said the meeting between Ramos and the party's
leading contenders for presidential nomination aims to "further
strengthen unity, teamwork and cohesion" within the ruling party.
</P>
<P>
There have been fears in the party that a fierce struggle for
the party's nomination and the endorsement of Ramos will possibly
split the administration camp like in the previous 1992 election.
</P>
<P>
In 1992, Ramos broke away from the then ruling Laban party and
formed the Lakas party after failing to be nominated by Laban
national convention. But Ramos won the election with the
anointment of former president Corazon Aquino.
</P>
<P>
Those invited to attend the meeting are the party's six
presidential contenders -- Speaker of the House of Representatives
Jose de Venecia, Senator Leticia Shahani, Defense Secretary Renato
de Villa, Presidential Adviser on Economic Affairs Emilio Osmena,
Finance Secretary Roberto de Ocampo and Senator Heherson Alvarez.
</P>
<P>
Also invited are Local Government Secretary Robert Barbers and
Chairman Manuel Morato of the Philippine Charity Sweepstakes, who
are aiming to be nominated as vice presidential candidate.
</P>
<P>
The party's 16-man ad hoc committee on electoral policy
formulation will also attend the meeting. The committee is
expected to brief the presidential aspirants on the progress of
the nomination and selection process being undertaken by the
ruling party.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is expected to clarify vital issues pertaining to
the mechanics and composition of the party's national convention
and the timing of Ramos endorsement for the presidential bet.
</P>
<P>
It will also discuss the conduct of nationwide pre-convention
consultations with Lakas members to determine party preferences
for the presidential nomination. 
</P>
</TEXT>
