<HEADLINE> Six Drug Traffickers Executed In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Six people, five of whom were
Hong Kong residents, were executed here today for smuggling and
dealing in drugs.
</P>
<P>
According to the verdict handed down by the Shenzhen
Intermediate People's Court, since 1993 they had been involved in
four separate illegal drug deals, making a large profit from
selling drugs in the inland areas.
</P>
<P>
The court revealed that one of the serious cases involved the
trafficking of 37,154 grams of heroin.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with Chinese law, because their crimes involved
the selling and smuggling of drugs, and because the sums involved
were very large and the criminal offence extremely serious, they
were given the death sentence. 
</P>
