<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Some 3,000 students graduated from
the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee's Party School,
today.
</P>
<P>
The school's president, Hu Jintao, who is a member of the
Standing Committee of the CPC Central Committee's Political
Bureau, spoke at the graduation ceremony and handed them their
certificates.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, over 2330 people graduated from the school's
state government and army branches.
</P>
<P>
Hu said that officials have the historical responsibility of
improving themselves and developing the Party. He asked the
graduates to carefully study an important speech made by President
Jiang Zemin at the school in May of this year and urged them to
uphold the banner of Deng Xiaoping. Party officials must implement
the Party's basic policy thoroughly, correctly, and actively, he
said, and get involved in the reforms and opening up and the
modernization drive wholeheartedly.
</P>
<P>
To build China into a prosperous, strong, democratic and
civilized country, they need strict criteria for themselves and
need to temper themselves, adhering to the Party's basic doctrine
of serving the people wholeheartedly. They must strengthen and
safeguard the unity of the Party consciously and must resist
corruption and promote clean government.
</P>
<P>
Hu went on to say that Deng's theory of building socialism with
Chinese characteristics is the guiding principle of the whole
Party, a spiritual pillar of the Chinese nation, and the
ideological weapon of every official. The relationship between them
and the people is one of fundamental stance, world outlook, and
Party spirit.
</P>
<P>
Correct political orientation must be maintained, and that
points in the direction of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics that represents the people's fundamental
interests. He urged them to place the people's interests foremost
while remaining consistent with the CPC Central Committee with
Jiang Zemin at its core. 
