to mark the official issuing of the Album of the PLA Hong Kong
Garrison.
</P>
<P>
Containing over 200 colored pictures, the album is divided into
six parts, covering Chinese leaders' care for the PLA garrison,
the formation of the troops and its glorious history.
</P>
<P>
The pictures also record various activities that took place
from June 30 to July 1 when the PLA troops entered Hong Kong to
take over the defense duties in the Special Administrative Region
(SAR).
</P>
<P>
Major General Xiong Ziren, political commissar of the garrison,
said at the ceremony that the publishing of the album is
significant in helping Hong Kong people know the PLA troops
stationed in Hong Kong, establishing close relations among the
military, the government and the civilians and promoting the
troops' development.
</P>
<P>
"Since the stationing of the troops in Hong Kong, the SAR
government and Hong Kong compatriots have shown great care and
support to the troops and provided necessary conditions for us to
effectively perform our duty," Xiong said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed thanks to the SAR government, social communities
and the press for this.
</P>
<P>
He said the troops will faithfully perform their duty, respect
and support the SAR government, and strictly abide by the national
and Hong Kong laws.
</P>
<P>
Vice Chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference Henry Fok Ying-tung, Chief
Executive of the HKSAR Tung Chee Hwa were among the many local
dignitaries present at the ceremony.
</P>
