<HEADLINE> New CD Published to Mark the Invention of Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, China's largest trade
and financial center, today released a CD to mark the 120th
anniversary of the invention of the phonograph record.
</P>
<P>
A limited number of 3,000 of the CDs, entitled "China
Phonograph Record Collection", were produced by the Shanghai
branch of the China Phonograph Corporation.
</P>
<P>
It contains 18 of the most typical pieces of original music
throughout China's recording history, and includes one of the
first foreign records brought into China at the end of the 19th
century, the first phonograph recorded in China in the early 20th
century, the "Yellow River Cantata", and many other classical
works.
</P>
<P>
Recording technology was invented by Thomas Edison on July 18,
1877 and was seen as the "Miracle of the 19th Century" and marked
the beginning of the world's recording business.
</P>
<P>
China's first phonograph record factory was set up in Shanghai
in 1908. 
</P>
</TEXT>
