<HEADLINE> Long-jumper Beckford Suspended for Doping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Olympic long jump runner-up James
Beckford of Jamaica has been suspended for three months following
his positive doping test result, the International Amateur
Athletic Federation (IAAF) said in Monaco on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Beckford tested positive for the stimulant ephedrien in June's
Paris Grand Prix, where he finished second, the IAAF said.
</P>
<P>
The IAAF said he is now pending a hearing where he has the
opportunity to explain the presence of the drug.
</P>
<P>
Beckford's appeal is not expected to be completed before the
world athletics championships which begin on August 1 in Athens,
Greece, the IAAF said. 
</P>
