<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- The People's Insurance Company of
China (PICC), the country's largest insurer, has reported a 40
percent growth in premium income, to reach 42.8 billion yuan,
in the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
Ma Yongwei, president and general manager of the company, said
here today that PICC's premium income generated from life insurance
business also hit 18.1 billion yuan in the first half, a jump of
707.5 percent over the same period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the company's sales of property insurance policies
have also hit 21 billion yuan, up 9.4 percent, he said.
</P>
<P>
PICC now has three subsidiaries, including PICC Life, PICC
Property and PICC Reinsurance. Each of the three companies is
playing a dominant role in their respective categories.
</P>
<P>
Ma said that PICC presently holds more than 70 percent of the
total shares of China's insurance market. In the first half of
this year, the company paid a total of 16.7 billion yuan to
cover compensation claims by insured Chinese.
</P>
<P>
"PICC will continue efforts in improving management and risk
control measures in the second half of this year, as a way to
consolidate and expand our shares in China's insurance market," Ma
said.
</P>
<P>
Insurance specialists said that China has great potential to be
tapped in insurance sector, and the total sales of insurance
policies are expected to top 250 billion yuan by the end of the
century.  
