<HEADLINE> Cotton Doing Well in North and Central China Provinces </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beijing, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Some 1.2 million ha of cotton, or
more than a quarter of China's total growing area this year, are
doing well in northern Hebei Province and central Henan Province,
statistics from the two provinces show.
</P>
<P>
Hybrid-seed areas accounted for 95 percent of the land planted,
while plastic sheeting was applied to nearly half this year's
cotton acreage, which are both guarantees of a good harvest under
normal conditions.
</P>
<P>
Hebei sent 4,000 technical personnel to the cotton fields to
help farmers improve management and fight the bollworm
disease. And the province sold agricultural equipment to cotton
growers on credit.
</P>
<P>
An anti-drought campaign is going strong in these two provinces.
</P>
<P>
China planted 4.5 million ha of cotton fields this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
