<DOCNO> XIE19970718.0074 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanxi to Hold Cultural and Tourism Festival on Merchants' Courtyards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, July 18 (Xinhua) --The first cultural and tourist
festival based on the theme of merchants' courtyards of ancient
dynasties, will be held in Qixian County of Shanxi Province from
July 20 to 26.
</P>
<P>
Qixian, together with Taigu, Pingyao, Jiexiu and Lingshi, which
are all situated in the central part of Shanxi Province, are
considered as the birthplace of Shanxi's commercial culture.
</P>
<P>
According to historical records, many of the businessmen who
had dominated the domestic and overseas business community from
the Ming Dynasty (1368-1644) to Qing Dynasty (1644-1911) made
their start here.
</P>
<P>
These businessmen built many grandiose courtyards of
distinctive styles in the heyday of their careers in central
Shanxi, and the places have now become a popular tourist
destination for visitors to Shanxi province, also a leading coal
producer in China.
</P>
<P>
During the festival, the organizing committee will arrange four
special tourist routes to ancient sites of courtyards built by
merchants and to museums featuring folk customs and folklore. Also
on the agenda are auctions of cultural goods and various cultural
performances.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970718.0075 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Manila, Muslim Rebels Sign General Ceasefire Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 18 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine government and the
rebel Moro Islamic Liberation Front (MILF) today signed an
agreement for general cessation of hostilities in the southern
Philippines.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed in Cagayan de Oro city by Fortunato
Abat, chief negotiator of the government peace panel, and MILF
vice chairman for political affairs Ghazali Jaafar.
</P>
<P>
Philippine Defense Secretary Renato de Villa and Executive
Secretary Ruben Torres and other representatives from both sides
witnessed the signing of the agreement.
</P>
<P>
As stated in the agreement, the two sides agreed to commit
their respective forces to a general ceasefire effectively July
21, direct their respective sub-committees on ceasefire to meet
and draw and finalize the guidelines and ground rules for the
implementation of the agreement.
</P>
<P>
They also decided to resume and proceed with the formal peace
talks in a venue to be mutually agreed upon by the two sides.
</P>
<P>
A 12,000-member rebel group, the MILF has been fighting
government troops in the southern Philippines. It entered
low-level peace talks with Manila earlier this year, but so far
the two sides made little progress in forging a peace agreement.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
