<HEADLINE> 2nd-Season Jobless Rate Falls in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's unemployment rate in
the second season of this year dropped slightly to 2.4 percent
while the underemployment rate, to 1.2 percent, the latest labor
force figures show.
</P>
<P>
The seasonally adjusted jobless rate for the period between
March and May of 1997 stood at 2.5 percent, while the
underemployment rate, at 1.3 percent, according to figures
released today by the Census and Statistics Department.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman of the department said that the decline in the
unemployment rate was mainly reflected in the construction, import
and export trade, restaurants and hotel sectors.
</P>
<P>
The overall labor demand remained robust in tandem with the
steady growth of the economy, added the spokesman. 
