Conference, met here today with a delegation from the Hong Kong
Young Industrialists Council led by its President Leung Wai Ho.
</P>
<P>
Wang, also head of the United Front Work Department of the
Central Committee of the Communist Party of China, said he was
very pleased to note that the Hong Kong Young Industrialists
Council sent its first delegation to the interior areas for a
visit after Hong Kong's return to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
He said the successful settlement of the Hong Kong issue by
peaceful means and the principle of "one country, two systems" have
set a good example for the world.
</P>
<P>
