people as well as the international community have more confidence
in Hong Kong's future, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said it is certain that there is much to be accomplished by
the Hong Kong industrialists and business people and their work will
be active and successful.
</P>
<P>
Leung said the delegation's visit following Hong Kong's return
to the motherland shows its members' firm belief in the earnest
implementation of the principle and policy of "one country, two
systems", "the Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong" and a high
degree of autonomy by the central people's government, as well as
their full confidence in Hong Kong's future.
</P>
<P>
He said the delegation will also conduct a study tour of Inner
Mongolia and Shaanxi Province to learn about economic
development there and explore the possibilities of cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Leung noted that these areas are rich in resources while Hong
Kong has kept widespread links with other parts of the world and
has advantages in capital, technology and information.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Council is willing to serve as a "bridge" in
promoting common development and prosperity in Hong Kong and
China's interior areas.
</P>
<P>
He said the Council will conduct various kinds of activities
for learning and implementing the Basic Law and make due
contributions to the promotion of peaceful reunification of the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
Wang praised the delegation members for their far-sightedness
in noticing unique advantages of and prospects for the country's
central and western areas.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that the delegation members will lead
more Hong Kong entrepreneurs in investing in these areas, in an
effort to boost the economy and explore their own opportunities.
</P>
