<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian Foreign Minister
Ung Huot will attend the ASEAN Ministerial Meeting (AMM) to be
held here next week, Malaysian Foreign Minister Abdullah Ahmad
Badawi said today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press briefing on preparations for the July 24-25
ASEAN ministerial meeting, Badawi reiterated the group's stand on
a coalition government between Cambodian First Prime Minister
Prince Norodom Ranariddh's FUNCINPEC Party and the Cambodian
People's Party led by Second Prime Minister Hun Sen.
</P>
