<HEADLINE> Zanzibar to Have Joint-Ventiure Airline </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Zanzibar Airlines - a
joint venture between the Isles government and investors from the
Gulf states - is in the offing, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
Moving her ministry's estimates for the 1997/98 fiscal year at
the House of Representatives in the town of Zanzibar Thursday,
the Minister for Finance, Amina Salim Ali, said the new airline
is expected to start its operations early next year.
</P>
<P>
The minister told the house that the government has finalised
work on the initial stages for the formation of the airline,
expected to facilitate and boost air transportation in both
domestic and international routes.
</P>
<P>
She further informed the house of on-going measures to
motivate investors which include making the Zanzibar Investment
Promotion Authority (ZIPA) into a "one stop center" and making
some amendments to the ZIPA Act of 1986.
</P>
<P>
The minister said a Management Information System (MIS) will
be established within ZIPA to obtain information on investment
opportunities from all over the world and classification of
investment records.
</P>
<P>
According to the minister, the system will enable potential
investors to get information on existing investment opportunities
through internet computers.
</P>
<P>
Another plan to be known as Local Area Network (LAN) will be
established at ZIPA to facilitate faster decision making within
the authority. 
</P>
