<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Manila No Longer Allows Media Interview with AIDS </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 18 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines' Department of
Health announced today that it would no longer allow the media to
interview victims of the Acquired Immune Deficiency Syndrome
(AIDS).
</P>
<P>
Jasmin Chipeco, chief of the department's regional office
technical services, said the Health Department would also no
longer disclose to the media the number of AIDS victims in the
country.
</P>
<P>
Chipeco said the Health Department adopted the strict policy to
protect the privacy and human rights of the AIDS victims.
</P>
<P>
She added that the Health Department would not like a
repetition of the case of AIDS victim Sarah Jane Salazar, who was
spoiled and exploited by the media.
</P>
<P>
Salazar was widely covered by the local media for her
cohabitation with a 17-year-old young man. She gave birth to her
second child last month. The young man was tested negative of the
AIDS at the present.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
