<DOCNO> XIE19970718.0118 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Electronic Industry Reports Steady Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- China's electronic industry
witnessed steady growth in the first six months this year, with
its output value totaling 162.6 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The figure represented a 26.5 percent increase from the same
period in 1996, according to statistics from China's Ministry of
Electronics Industry (MEI).
</P>
<P>
Of the different products manufactured during the period, China
in the first six months produced 650,000 personal computers, an
increase of 27.5 percent; automatic telephone switchboards with a
total capacity of 7.21 million lines, up 29.8 percent; and 10.44
million TV sets, a rise of 12 percent.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the customs houses indicated that exports of
Chinese-produced electronics products shot up 24 percent during
that period to 11 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, sales of China's electronics industry are estimated
at 99 billion yuan, a rise of 18 percent. The production to sales
ratio was around 94 percent.
</P>
<P>
According to sources from MEI, the electronics departments and
enterprises nationwide in the period redoubled their efforts to
improve key products, projects and enterprises, which can yield
good economic returns.
</P>
<P>
Centered around the state information projects, developers
under the ministry developed a contingent of new systems, software
and network products, as well as other electronics tools for the
work.
</P>
<P>
In the consumer market, large-screen TV sets, video compact disc
(VCD) players and digital audio components enjoyed brisk market
sales in the first six months.
</P>
<P>
Other electronics for automobile, communication, electric and
medicine industries, also were big boosters for local electronics
sectors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
