<HEADLINE> Manila, Macao to Strengthen Cooperation in Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Philippine Tourism Secretary Mina
Gabor and his Macao counterpart signed here today a memorandum of
understanding in tourism cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Gabor said after the signing ceremony that the paper is
expected to strengthen the friendly relations and mutual
understanding between Manila and Macao.
</P>
<P>
According to the memorandum, Macao should launch an intensive
drive to promote every tourism attraction in the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
The memorandum also stated that individual and group travel,
the exchange of visits between professional experts and the
exchange of information and experiences on tourism will be
encouraged between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
Tourism-related establishment, particularly travel agencies,
will be encouraged to establish business contacts and exchange
experiences, the memorandum said. 
</P>
