<HEADLINE> 398 Kinds of Shares Listed at Shanghai Stock Exchange </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 18 (Xinhua) -- A total of 398 kinds of shares
have been listed on the Shanghai Stock Exchange since SSE, China's
first stock trading exchange, opened for business in 1990.
</P>
<P>
The most-recently listed company is the Guangzhou Electrical
Enterprise Group, which had its 90 million shares listed here
beginning from today.
</P>
<P>
Information from SSE said that of the total, 353 kinds are A
shares, or those shares targeted at domestic investors, and 45 B
shares which are designed for overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
Listed companies are engaged in a wide range of production
from agricultural, industrial to service trade sectors, 70
percent of which are from areas outside Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The Shenzhen Stock Exchange in Shenzhen, Guangdong Province,
has also been expanding rapidly since the beginning of this
year. It now handles trading of 360 kinds of shares, 90 of which
were floated in the 115 trading days in the first half of the
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
