<HEADLINE> Big Tin-Plated Steel Sheet Mill Operational </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 18 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Yichang Tin-plated
Steel Sheet Mill, with an investment of 410 million yuan (about
51.25 million US dollars), went into operation today.
</P>
<P>
The mill, a key industrial project in Shanghai,is designed to
ease the imbalance between supply and demand of tin-plated steel
sheets in the country, and will also cut imports, experts say.
</P>
<P>
Advanced equipment and control systems for the mill are from
the U.S. and Germany.  
</P>
</TEXT>
