<HEADLINE> NZ Stocks Finish Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, July 18 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
finished lower today in response to a sharp rise in short-term
interest rates.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 index ended 19 points lower at 2,475 with a heavy
turnover of 98 million NZ dollars (64 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Telecom shares, sensitive to short-term interest rates, slumped
21 cents to 745 cents. Also lower were Fletcher Forests, down 3c
to 195c, Fletcher Building, dropping 5c to 430c, Fletcher Paper,
dipping 1c to 343c, and Lion Nathan, falling 1c to 379c.
</P>
<P>
Among other leaders, Carter Holt Harvey and Brierley Investment
both remained steady at 370c and 137c respectively.
</P>
<P>
But Fletcher Energy gained 4c to 487c and Air New Zealand edged
up 1c to 309c.
</P>
<P>
There were 63 falls and 45 rises.  
</P>
</TEXT>
