<HEADLINE> Gangsu's Largest Labor Market Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, July 18 (Xinhua) -- The largest labor market in
northwest China's Gansu Province opened today in this capital city
of Gansu.
</P>
<P>
The 1,300-sq m market will provide services for people who are
job-hunting or want to change work units. The market has been
connected with a nationwide computer network which offers
information about the available part-time and full-time jobs
through a huge electronic screen in the market hall.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the market will also provide information on
social security, re-employment and talent training programs.
