<DOCNO> XIE19970718.0138 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Unified Labor Market Taking Shape </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 18 (Xinhua) -- A unified labor market is taking
shape in China's largest industrial city of Shanghai, where
157,000 laid-off workers were recruited through employment
agencies in 1996, according to official figures.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, over 430 such agencies have been set up in the city
to provide job opportunities as well as professional training
and consultation.
</P>
<P>
All major job markets in the city are computerized, and the
Shanghai TV Station has joined the market by broadcasting 600
items of job-related information every day.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the municipal government is now releasing forecasts
on the supply and demand of laborers. The three most common job
vacancies are for shop assistants, cashiers and hotel attendants.
</P>
<P>
And job consultation, which has appeared along with the
expanding labor market, has become a new profession in
Shanghai. There are currently nearly 3,000 consultants in the city
and at least 30,000 locals have been re-employed with help from
the experts.
</P>
<P>
The formation of the local labor market has also accelerated
the pace of bankrupting and merging of local money-losing
enterprises. By the end of 1996, 58 state firms had declared
bankruptcy and more than 730 local companies had been merged,
which has saved nearly eight billion yuan-worth of idle assets of
state companies.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970718.0139 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chang Surges to Reach Quarter-Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 17 (Xinhua) -- World number two Michael Chang
surged to beat 163rd-ranked American player Michael Joyce 4-6,
6-1, 6-2 here Thursday to reach the quarter-finals of the ATP
Washington Classic tennis.
</P>
<P>
Top-seed Chang is seeking a tour-best fifth title of the year
in his first hardcourt tournament since winning in April. The
current 675,000-dollar Washington event is the first warm-up for
the U.S.Open which will be held five-and-a-half weeks later.
</P>
<P>
It was his second three-set-match after his tough struggle
against Mexican Luis Herrera in the second round.
</P>
<P>
Chang advanced to a Friday showdown with 66th-ranked Scott
Draper of Australia. Draper, who beat American Steve Campbell 6-3,
7-6 (9/7), is 1-1 against Chang.
</P>
<P>
Second-seed Petr Korda ensured his return to the world's top-20
after an absence of almost two-and-a-half years, beating Dutchman
Fernon Wibier 6-4, 6-4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
