<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Red Cross delegates from the
Democratic People's Republic of Korea and South Korea will meet in
Beijing on July 23 to handle the South's direct delivery of the
second batch of private-level food aid to the North.
</P>
<P>
Kang Young-hoon, Chairman of the South Korean National Red
Cross (KNRC), told his North counterpart over the phone today that
the KNRC agreed on the time and the venue for the talks.
</P>
<P>
