Talks in the truce village of Panmunjom or other convenient place
inside South Korea on July 22.
</P>
<P>
Correspondingly, the Red Cross Society of the DPRK on Tuesday
replied that it's again favoring Beijing as the venue for the
General Secretary-level contact on July 23.
</P>
<P>
The talks will be resumed after about two months since May 26,
when South Korea agreed to donate 50,000 tons of grain to the
North by the end of this month in the first stage.
</P>
<P>
At the coming Beijing meeting, the South side plans to bring up
such issues as the timing and scale of the second-stage food aid.
</P>
