Yubamrung said in parliament that he had ordered the raids because
the firms were believed to have sent fax messages to the United
States, France, Britain, Hong Kong and Singapore about five banks'
imminent close-down.
</P>
<P>
Managers of the two brokerage firms denied they were involved
in spreading the rumor.
</P>
<P>
