<HEADLINE> World Bank Assists Poverty-reduction Project in Argentina </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 17 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today approved a
75 million U.S. dollar loan to finance the Small Farmer
Development Project in Argentina.
</P>
<P>
The project will assist the Argentine government's strategy to
reduce rural poverty by improving the productive and
organizational capacity of poor rural communities and
strengthening national and provincial rural development policy.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the project is estimated at 108 million
dollars. Most of the money will be used to finance a rural
investment component which includes a small grants fund to provide
technical and financial assistance for the implementation of
demand-driven investments aimed at supporting productive
activities of the poor. The project will also provide technical
assistance and training to support improved rural development
strategy and program development.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the World Bank loan, the Argentine government will
contribute 25 million dollars and the remaining 8 million dollars
will come from beneficiaries. 
