<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Largest Bronze Coin Found in Yunnan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Archaeologists have found China's
largest ancient bronze coin in Huize County, Yunnan Province.
</P>
<P>
The 450-year-old coin has a perimeter of 181.78 centimeters, a
diameter of 57.8 centimeters and an aperture with a diameter of
10.24 centimeters.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that the coin is known as the "Jiajing Tongbao"
issued during the reign of Emper Jiajing (1522-1566m of the Ming
Dynasty (1368-1644).
</P>
<P>
The coin, which weighs 41.5 kilograms, is the largest among
ancient coins discovered so far.
</P>
<P>
Huize County is the home of an ancient bronze smelting center,
historians said.
</P>
<P>
Archaeologists said that the commemorative bronze coin is of
value to the study of ancient coin casting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
