<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Central Bank Tightens Financial Supervision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 18 (Xinhua) -- The People's Bank of China, the
central bank, has promulgated a set of rules to improve financial
supervision and perfect internal control in financial
organizations.
</P>
<P>
The rules consist of the planning, operation and reporting on
the bank's financial supervision, and will enable the bank to
improve its overall supervision over the financial market by
providing clear guidance as to what the bank should accomplish
through the whole procedure, said a central bank official.
</P>
<P>
The rules regard the financial control by the central bank as
an inseparable part of its work, and call for smooth information
exchanges and close cooperation between its supervisory body and
other departments.
</P>
<P>
In another effort to improve its financial control, the central
bank issued regulations governing the settlement through credit
card, which will go into effect in August.
</P>
<P>
The regulations stipulate that only commercial banks and their
branches with central bank approval may handle the business of
settlement through credit card, which is restricted to financial
transfer and can't be used for cash withdrawal.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, unauthorized commercial banks, urban and rural
cooperative banks and other non-financial institutions are banned
from the business. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
