<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Traditional Uygur Art Rediscovered </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, July 18 (Xinhua) -- This capital of the Xinjiang Uygur
Autonomous Region has held an ethnic art exhibition to showcase
the charm of "Mukamu," the internationally-popular folk music of
the Uygur people.
</P>
<P>
The show features photos, pictures and live performances by
local Mukamu musicians.
</P>
<P>
Mukamu is centered in a number of countries and regions in
North Africa, and Central, East and South Asia. The Uygur Mukamu,
with the most and widest variety of pieces, is recognized as the
"musical pearl along the Silk Road" both in China and abroad.
</P>
<P>
The representative work, the Twelve Mukamu, is composed of
twelve lengthy classical compositions with 360 melodies.
</P>
<P>
Since the establishment of New China in 1949, the local
governments have set up special organizations to collect the folk
music.
</P>
<P>
Over the past few years, the Uygur Mukamu has been performed at
the Chinese Art Festival, the Northwest China's Music Week and
some other events throughout the nation.
</P>
<P>
It is also highly praised by foreigners when performed in
Britain, Germany, Japan and many other countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970718.0183 </DOCNO>
