<HEADLINE> Explosion Occurs Near SFOR Base in Bosnia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, July 17 (Xinhua) -- An explosion occurred Wednesday
night near a base of the Multinational Stabilization Force (SFOR)
in the Bosnian Serb-controlled town of Banja Luka, SFOR command in
southwestern Bosnia said today.
</P>
<P>
The explosion was caused by three hand grenades thrown at the
SFOR base and no one was seriously injured, the Tanjug news agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
SFOR guards found that two people left with a car immediately
after the explosion and four suspects have been detained.
</P>
<P>
The Banja Luka police said that the incident is still under
investigation.
</P>
<P>
This is the eighth explosion since the SFOR shot dead one war
crime suspect who resisted arrest on July 10 in Prijedor, near
Banja Luka. 
</P>
