<DOCNO> XIE19970718.0186 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Employees in Shijiazhuang Pleased With Medical Insurance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, July 18 (Xinhua) -- A medical insurance system is
now in place for the 130,000 employees of government offices and
State-owned enterprises and institutions in the capital city of
north China's Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
It's a switch from the former medical care system, under which
those working for the government or State-owned enterprises and
institutions received medical treatment funded entirely by the
State.
</P>
<P>
The new system is based on a medical insurance fund set up
with an initial investment from the local government, into which
every unit turns in an amount equivalent to 10 percent of the
total waves of all its employees for the previous year, while
each employee pays one percent of his wages or salary.
</P>
<P>
Every person participating in the project has his own medical
account in the bank, and is entitled to reimbursement for medical
expenses, said Xing Hongshan, director of Hebei's Medical
Insurance Managing Center.
</P>
<P>
He added that people are no longer limited to only one or two
hospitals as they used to be. They can go to any hospital included
on the hospital's computer network.
</P>
<P>
The network can report violations of regulations to the center
at any time and can be used to audit the medical accounts and to
provide information about medical insurance.
</P>
<P>
China started to reform its medical care system in the
1980s, since the former State-subsidized system, which came into
being in the early 1950s when a planned economy was practiced
in China, was putting too much strain on State and local coffers.
</P>
<P>
Shijiazhuang is the first provincial capital among the 58
cities chosen to adopt medical insurance.
</P>
<P>
By the end of this year, those who enjoy free medical care in
the city will have changed to the new medical insurance and the
system soon will be introduced to urban and rural residents across
the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970718.0187 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-18 </DATE_TIME>
