<HEADLINE> Forty-One Banks Held Up in Mexico City in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Bank robbers have looted more
than 12 million pesos (about 1.6 million U.S. dollars) from 41
bank holdups in the Federal District of Mexico this year.
</P>
<P>
A report from the General Direction of Investigation of Bank
Heists and Organized Crime and the Attorney General of the
Republic (PGR) said that of the total only 60,000 dollars have
been recovered.
</P>
<P>
It says there is a 7.4 percent increase in bank assaults so far
this year, compared with the same period of 1996. But the money
robbed from 38 bank loots last year was 14 million pesos (about
1.8 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
Thirty-five persons have been detained so far this year on
charges of bank robbery and 31 guns were confiscated. Four people
were reportedly killed. 
</P>
