<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Violence the Main Cause of Death in America </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, July 17 (Xinhua) -- More than 1,250 people were
killed and thousands more seriously injured in violence every day
in the American Continent, according to a study by the
Pan-American Health Organization (OPS).
</P>
<P>
The study, published here today, said violence in Latin
American and the Caribbean countries has become one of the main
causes of death.
</P>
<P>
The document, drafted by Rodrigo Guerrero, OPS regional
counselor on Health and Violence, says that in the United States
alone, 65 people are assassinated every day and more than 6,000
injured in violence.
</P>
<P>
The average rate of violence in the continent is 20 per 100,000
persons, much higher than other regions of the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
