<HEADLINE> Heavier Penalty to Be Imposed on Drug Money Laundering </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Licensing tougher penalty for people
laundering money from drug dealings, the Karlsruhe-based German
Supreme Court today ruled that they could be punished as drug
traffickers, according to reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
It ordered trial courts to take a tougher stance on three
defendants charged with laundering proceeds from the drug trade,
saying their activities had "promoted" drug trafficking.
</P>
<P>
In Germany, people can be sentenced to up to 10 years in prison
for money laundering, but up to 15 years for drug trafficking.
</P>
