<HEADLINE> 18 Killed in Road Accident in Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Eighteen people were killed and 26
others wounded when a truck turned over Tuesday on the road from
Angola's coastal city Benguela to the capital Luanda, the Angola
National News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The police said that overload was the main reason for the
serious accident, while the driver argued that disorder of the
brake caused the overturn of the truck which was on the downhill
path.
</P>
<P>
Local doctors said that the number of the dead will increase
as some victims were injured seriously.
</P>
<P>
The accident spot on the road from Benguela to Luanda, 15
kilometers away from Sumbe City in Kwanza-Sul Province, has been
regarded as a dangerous site, where 10 accidents have happened
this year,leaving 40 people dead and over 80 wounded. 
</P>
