<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Software Moves Talkers Out of Chaotic Chat Rooms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Now people are able to move out
of the chaotic chat room on the Internet and enter a more personal
on-line chat, with the introduction of some new software.
</P>
<P>
Until recently, if people want to enter a talk with someone
over the net, he or she has to first get into a chat room where
dozens of people talking things of their interest, a difficult
environment for a discussion just between two or three.
</P>
<P>
The Wall Street Journal reported that there is a new kind of
chat designed for one-to-one communication with someone you know.
These new chat setups are more like a phone call with a friend or
colleague.
</P>
<P>
Consumers say they are finding myriad uses for small, private
on-line discussions. Some companies see opportunities to build the
capability into business software.
</P>
<P>
Before long, advocates say, electronic chats will seem as
indispensable as electronic mail, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
About a half-dozen companies have put up such software on the
Internet for free downloading. They say that several million users
are already chatting away, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
The instant reply of on-line chat provides more convenience
than e-mail, in which the mail sender seldom knows whether his or
her message has been received and read. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
