<HEADLINE> ANC Official Appeals for Peaceful Solution to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 17 (Xinhua) --A senior official of South
Africa's ruling African National Congress (ANC) today called on
the Kenyan government to find a peaceful solution to turmoils in
the country.
</P>
<P>
"Africa has no space for political problems to be solved
through force, " ANC National Executive Committee member Blade
Nzimande told a press conference.
</P>
<P>
During the past several weeks, Kenya has experienced the worst
political unrest in recent years as opposition parties have
repeatedly organized mass rallies in the country to press for
minimum constitutional reforms before the coming general
elections.
</P>
<P>
At least nine people were reportedly killed in clashed between
demonstrators and the police a few days ago.
</P>
<P>
Nzimande stressed that human rights remained integral to the
ANC's foreign policy, adding that South Africa would take its cue
from organizations such as the Organization of African Unity and
the United Nations in condemning human rights violations. 
</P>
