<HEADLINE> S.Leonean Delegation Arrives in Capital of Cote </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FREETOWN, July 17 (Xinhua) -- A 12- man delegation sent by the
Sierra leonean junta arrived in Abidjan, capital of Cote
d'Ivoire, late Wednesday to start talks with the ECOWAS mediation
commission wihich is seeking an end to seven weeks of political
impasse in Sierra Leone where the military overthrew the civilian
government on May 25.
</P>
<P>
The talks are expected to start Thursdday and theire is no
indication as to how long they would last.
</P>
<P>
The delegation, led by the junta's Foreign Secretary Paolo
Bangura, included Attorney-General Manley Spaine, Chief of
Military Staff Daniel Anderson, Head of the rebel Revolutionary
United Foront's war councli, Solomon Rogers and Secrertary to the
head of state Sheky Bayoh.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, ECOMOG officials in Freetown said a truce has been
signed with officials of the Sierra Leone army to end bloody
clashes that have left over 150 civilians dead.
</P>
<P>
The latest of the clashes took place last weekend at Jui, near
the captial, which government officials said, were provoked by
fighter jets belonging to ECOMOG which flew low level altitudes
over the capital.
</P>
<P>
All is reported quiet in the Jui area, about 17 miles east of
the capptial but the main road Aw Waterloo leading to other parts
of the interrrior remained blocked by Nigerian troops.
</P>
<P>
In another development, an anti-Nigerian army mass rally has
been held at the national stadium in the capital Thursday which
was attended by thousands of people.
</P>
<P>
Speaker after speaker denouncded the presnece of Nigerian
troops in Sierra Leone and called for the ''immediate
withdrawal'' of the Nigerian troops.
</P>
<P>
Banners displayed carried messages such as '' Down With
Abacha,'' ''Abacha is trying to get a colony in west Africa'',
'' Nigerian troops stop killing our women and children'' and ''
Who gave Nigeria the right to hold on to our airport ?''.
</P>
</TEXT>
