<HEADLINE> Salim, Mugabe Discuss OAU Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Secretary-general of the
Organization of African Unity (OAU) Salim Ahmed Salim said here
today that efforts are being made to reform the organization in a
bid to make it more effective.
</P>
<P>
Salim told reporters after meeting OAU Executive Chairman,
Zimbabwean President Robert Mugabe that their discussions had
centered on tasks the new OAU leadership would have to tackle.
</P>
<P>
This was the first meeting between Salim and Mugabe since
their reappointment and appointment respectively to their
respective posts at the recent OAU summit.
</P>
<P>
Salim said the OAU would recruit a firm of consultants soon to
look into how best the structures could be reformed.
</P>
<P>
"We are in the process of looking at how it can adapt to the
challenges of the new millennium," he said.
</P>
<P>
Salim said the OAU would be sending a delegation of observers
to Liberia which would hold its presidential elections on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders also discussed developments in conflict-ridden
countries of Congo (Brazzaville), Sierra Leone, the Horn of
Africa, and the state affairs in the new Democratic Republic of
Congo.
</P>
<P>
Salim said, "our major concern is the promotion of stability
and security on the African continent."  
</P>
