<HEADLINE> Russian Envoy Arrives in Cyprus for Peace Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Russia's special envoy on Cyprus
Vladimir Tchizhov arrived here today for talks with Cypriot
President Glafcos Clerides and Turkish Cypriot leader Rauf
Denktash.
</P>
<P>
He told reporters upon his arrival that the purpose of his
visit is to continue the meetings he had in New York with the two
leaders and exchange views with them on the outcome of the first
round of direct talks between Clerides and Denktash which was
held in Troutbeck, near New York, from July 9 to 12.
</P>
<P>
"The agreement to hold a second round of talks means that
the first round was not a failure," the Russian envoy said.
</P>
<P>
The second round of U.N.-led face-to-face talks between
Clerides and Denktash is scheduled to take place in Montreux,
Switzerland, on August 11-16.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the European Commission's affirmation that EU's
accession talks with Cyprus will start next year, Tchizhov said
that it adds a new element to efforts for a solution to the
Cyprus problem.
</P>
<P>
The Cyprus issue has remained unresolved since 1974 when the
island was divided into Greek Cypriot South and Turkish Cypriot
North after the Turkish troops took over the northern third of
the island in the wake of a coup seeking union with Greece by
some Greek Cypriots. 
</P>
</TEXT>
