<HEADLINE> UK High Divorce Rate Blamed for Drink Toll </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Britain's divorce rate, which is
the highest in Europe, is believed to be part of the causes for a
rise in deaths from drink-related diseases in the country.
</P>
<P>
Jonathan Chick, a leading specialist in alcohol dependency and
senior lecturer at Edinburgh University, said Wednesday that
alcohol is increasingly a problem among the UK's single parents
and people living on their own.
</P>
<P>
On launching the first guidelines to help doctors to identify
and to treat heavy drinkers, Chick noted that in the past decade,
the number of UK people dying from alcohol-related diseases has
doubled while the rate has fallen in America and many European
countries.
</P>
<P>
He said that a partial explanation of this seems to be that
Britain has the highest divorce rate in Europe, with a rising
proportion of people living alone.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that in Britain, up to 30 percent of male
admission and 15 percent of female admission to surgical and
medical wards are for alcohol-related diseases. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
