<HEADLINE> Zanzibar to Charge More for Airport, Port Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, July 17 (Xinhua) -- The Zanzibar government
plans to raise airport and port service charges and introduce new
taxes on both sea tickets and luggage in an effort to boost
revenue collection.
</P>
<P>
Iddi Pandu Hassan, minister of State in the Chief-Minister's
Office for Constitution and Legal Affairs, told reporters in the
town of Zanzibar today that the plans are contained in amendments
of the budget on revenue collection to be presented to the House
of Representatives next week by Finance Minister Amina Salim Ali.
</P>
<P>
If the bill sails through, Hassan said, airport service
charges will shoot up to 2,000 Tanzania Shillings (about 3.2 U.S.
Dollars) from 1,0 T. Shs. (about 1.6 Dollars), while port
service charges up to 500 T. Shs. (about 0.8 Dollar) from 300 T.
Shs. (about 0.48 Dollar). Foreigners would pay five US Dollars as
port service charge.
</P>
<P>
The government also wants to impose a five percent sales tax
on each sea passenger ticket and luggage.
</P>
<P>
In the bill, the government further proposes that applications
by investors seeking exemptions on their investment projects set
up in Zanzibar would be charged five percent of the tax while the
remaining applications seeking exemptions would be charged two
percent of the tax. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
