efforts from stake-holders in the utilization of the country's
untapped resources," the president stressed.
</P>
<P>
Zambia should not depend on the international community to
reduce its poverty because the country has the potential to
generate its own wealth, Chiluba pointed out.
</P>
<P>
He said his government will soon reorganize the informal
sector so that it can create more job opportunities.
</P>
