<DOCNO> XIE19970718.0251 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Togolese President to Mediate on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Togolese Foreign
Minister Koffi Panou reaffirmed here today that President
Gnassingbe Eyadema has promised to mediate on the Bakassi
conflict between Nigeria and Cameroun.
</P>
<P>
Panou made the statement to the press here this afternoon
after a brief meeting with Camerounian Prime Minister Peter
Mafany Musonge.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria and Cameroun have fought fiercely on several occasions
over the oil-rich Bakassi peninsula in the Gulf of Guinea and
later put the issue to the International Court in Hague for
arbitration.
</P>
<P>
Panou said his current visit was also designed to strengthen
the fraternal relations existing between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The Togolese Foreign Minister also had discussions with the
Camerounian Premier on global issues, particularly some hot spots
on the African continent, Panou added.
</P>
<P>
As special envoy for Togolese President Gnassingbe Eyadema,
Panou also forwarded an undisclosed message from President
Eyadema to Camerounian President Paul Biya during the visit.
</P>
<P>
The envoy also stressed the need for African leaders to meet
regularly in order to resolve their differences through peaceful
means. 
</P>
</TEXT>
