<HEADLINE> European Shares End Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 17 (Xinhua) -- All shares on Europe's major stock
markets finished lower on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Britain's FTSE-100 index was dragged modestly lower as
profit-taking hit the drugs sector, but the market ended well off
the day's lows after faltering on the brink of the 5,000 hurdle.
The blue-chip index finished 15.2 points lower at 4,949.0.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, shares ended lower, having fallen sharply in
high-volume late afternoon trade. The IBIS DAX index closed at
4,203.91, down 19.78 points.
</P>
<P>
Shares on the Paris market ended sharply lower on profit-taking
triggered by an all-time record above the 3,000 level which caused
a barrage of sell stop orders from the futures market. The CAC-40
index closed at 2,958.59, down 29.42 points.  
</P>
</TEXT>
