<HEADLINE> New York Stocks Retreat Modestly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Stocks on Wall Street fell
modestly today in heavy trading as investors netted some profits
from Wednesday's rally, which put the Dow Jones industrial average
above 8,000 for the first time.
</P>
<P>
The Dow fell by 18.11 to 8,020.77.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a 9-to-8 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with NYSE volume totaling 629.06
million shares, down from 646.03 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list fell 5.01 to 931.58, and
the NYSE composite index fell 2.28 to 482.96.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index fell 11.65 to 1,568.98, and the
American Stock Exchange composite index fell 0.69 at 637.34.
</P>
<P>
Broad-market indicators also pulled back slightly as interest
rates moved higher from Wednesday's seven-month low in the bond
market.
</P>
<P>
The market was not very much moved by the news of more company
gains. But investors are waiting for the results of Microsoft
which will be released after the closing bell.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, technology shares led a broad rally spurred by a
mixture of more good news on company profits, inflation and
interest rates. The Dow gained 63 points, breaking above the
8,000-barrier less than 2 years and 4 months after it first
crossed 4,000.
</P>
<P>
There was little reaction to today's economic news, which
included a 4.8 percent increase of June's housing starts and a
drop in first claims of jobless benefits last week.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
